课程编码：S11004X 英文名称：Fate of Contaminants and Ecotoxicology 课时：60 学分：2.00 课程属性：学科基础课 主讲教师：刘双江等

教学目的要求
The aim of the course is to give a fundamental introduction to the fate processes and ecotoxicology. Physicochemical properties, distribution,
transport, transformation processes and ecotoxicological effects of natural and anthropogenic contaminants in water, air and soil are introduced.

When the course is finished the student is supposed to be able to:

Knowledge:
 Explain the fundamental principles and processes of the fate of contaminants in soil, water and air
 Describe the properties and the fate of a given contaminant in the environment
 Describe the transport of contaminants in soil and what variables that influence the transport
 Describe the variables and processes that are critical for the sensitivity of the ecosystem to natural and anthropogenic stress
 Reflect upon the criteria for toxicity, contamination and stability of the ecosystem
 Explain the fundamental ecotoxicological principles
 Quantify a specific contaminant’s speciation, availability, mobility, transport and ecotoxicology by the use of standard calculations

Skills:
 Evaluate the physicochemical properties, fate and environmental effect of natural and anthropogenic contaminants from environmental and ecotoxicological data
 Evaluate the critical variables and methods that may be used to quantify a contaminant’s distribution, transformation rates, transport and biological effect in the soil‐water‐air system

Competences:
 Conduct a scientific evaluation of the environmental and ecotoxicological effects of a contaminant
 Cooperate with fellow students on preparation and completion of a written report

预修课程
None

教材
vanLoon, G.A. and Duffy, S.J. (2010) Environmental Chemistry a global perspective. 3. Ed. Oxford University Press

Schwarzenbach, R.P. et al. (2005) Environmental Organic Chemistry, 2nd. Ed., Wiley, chapt. 14

Stephenson G.R. and Solomon K.R 2007, Pesticides and the Environment, CNTC Canadian Network of Toxicology Centres.

Copping, L.G. and Hewitt, H.G. 1998, Chemistry and Mode of Action of Crop Protection Agents. Royal Society of Chemistry, Cambridge, UK. Handout notes and journal papers.

Excursion material

主要内容
The course gives an introduction to the processes and properties that determine the fate and effect of contaminants in environmental systems with the main focus on the aquatic and terrestrial chemistry and to a lesser extent atmospheric chemistry. A review of contaminant groups is given including heavy metals, nanoparticles, microbial contaminants, organic xenobiotics and natural toxins. This includes:

‐ The influence of the contaminant’s physicochemical properties to the sorption, bioavailability, degradation, transport and biological effect
‐ The basic theory of ecotoxicology focusing on quantification of toxicity on biolabel, individual, population, and ecosystem level. The use of dose‐response curves to determine the toxicity
‐ Calculation methods for determination of concentration, speciation, sorption, degradation, ecotoxicity and transport
‐ The structure and physicochemical properties of the three spheres are treated.

教学目的要求
By the end of the course, students will be expected (1) to have understood the logic underling some basic statistic procedures, (2) to have taken the ability to choose appropriate statistic methods according to specific conditions, such as data type and experiment design etc.
Students will be expected to have become proficient enough to do a number of frequently used procedures:

Linear and nonlinear regression models,

Analysis of variance models

Mixed models

Multivariate methods

Graphical presentation of data

None

主要内容
This course is intended to give students, who have not taken introductory statistics previously, the fundamental knowledge, basic computing skills of data analysis and statistics, which are necessary to their future research.

课程编码：S11006X 英文名称：Hydrologic/Hydrographic Decision Support System 课时：60 学分：2.00 课程属性：学科基础课 主讲教师：陈求稳

教学目的要求
Learning objectives:
A student who has met the objectives of the course will be able to:
 Analyse a water flow modeling problem, reformulate it using differential polynomials and solve it using Ritt‐Wu’s characteristic set method;
 Perform hydrological mapping using airborne thermal infrared imagery: from orthorectification to radiative transfer model through atmospheric correction;
 Design a spatial database using a spatial database management system to store all the hydrologic/hydrographic data, that will be used in the hydrology/hydrographic decision support system;
 Perform basic spatial algorithms involved in water flow modeling;
 Use a water flow modeler and a 3D GIS to visualize the flow of a water column or a flooding;
 Integrate different flow modeling, 3D GIS and 3D visualizing software in a hydrographic decision support system.

预修课程
None

教材
To be decided

主要内容
1. Introduction to planar representations of the Earth
2. Ritt‐Wu’s characteristic set for systems of polynomial equations or systems of polynomial Partial Differential Equations (algebraico differential ideals)
3. Hydrologic ressources mapping using thermal infrared photogrammetry
4. GIS life cycle ‐ DSS life cycle
5. Spatio‐temporal data representation, storage, access methods and query
6. Spatial Algorithms with applications in Hydrologic/hydrographic Decision Support Systems (Digital Terrain Models, river basin determination, water flow modeling, water column visualization in 3D/4D)
7. Introduction and examples to flood modeling with GIS

课程名称: 创新、创造与企业精神的当代理论
英文名称: Contemporary Theory of Innovation, Creativity and Entrepreneurship
详细内容:
创新、创造与企业精神的当代理论

课程编码：S31001X 英文名称：Contemporary Theory of Innovation, Creativity and Entrepreneurship 课时：60 学分：2.00 课程属性：学科基础课 主讲教师：-

教学目的要求
The learning objectives for the module are that the student upon completion can:
- Define, analyze and reflect on key concepts within the discipline.
- Contextualize scientific insights into innovation practice (cases).

预修课程

教材

主要内容
The aim of module 1 is to give students a broad understanding of the dominant theories of innovation, creativity and entrepreneurship and how these theories interact and create dynamics, both at a macro-, meso- and micro level.

参考文献

课程教师信息

方法论

课程编码：S31004X 英文名称：Methodology 课时：60 学分：2.00 课程属性：学科基础课 主讲教师：王谦

教学目的要求
The learning objectives for the module are that the student after the end of this module can:
- Define and compare alternative scientific paradigms.
- Define and discuss strengths and weaknesses with alternative methods for data collection and analyze data both quantitatively and qualitatively.
- Apply methods in practice through exercises.

预修课程

教材

主要内容
The goal of module 4 is to give students a basic understanding of scientific paradigms and methodologies and their application to scientific- and practical problems. This contains the core theories for creation and reflection of acquired knowledge. This will strengthen the student’s ability to independently select and use methodological approaches that are most relevant in the context of specific development projects.
